    "body": "### Problem\n\n(This overlaps with other in-flight things like https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/33771 , but I'm creating this to have a focused artifact.)\n\nIf the user has things like `.git` or `package.json` in their HOME directory, LSP client will happily treat that as a root dir if the config has `root_markers = { '.git', 'package.json' }` ([example](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/issues/4209#issuecomment-3564311371)).\n\nHOME dir as a root dir is 99.9% of the time NOT intended, and is probably the cause of 50% or more of the \"performance issues\" that confuse users.\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIn `vim.lsp` core, never treat HOME dir as a \"root dir\", unless it was explicitly listed as a filename pattern. Something like this (drawing from helix's lsp config):\n\n    filetypes = { '~/*' }\n\nTasks\n\n- Merge https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/33771\n- Introduce the ability to define filename patterns in `filetypes`",
